From 30a34ceec50b7bbcf5ee466d13608ed36c597ca6 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Stanislav Kinsburskii <skinsburskii@linux.microsoft.com>
Date: Mon, 27 Jan 2025 11:25:27 -0800
Subject: [PATCH 109/124] lvbs.config: Add CONFIG_MODULE_SIG dependency

LVBS boot doesn't make much sense without modules signature verification as
VTL1 kernel won't be able to sign any modules, which will likely lead to
missing network, ob lock device, etc.

Signed-off-by: Stanislav Kinsburskii <skinsburskii@linux.microsoft.com>
---
 Microsoft/lvbs.config | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/Microsoft/lvbs.config b/Microsoft/lvbs.config
index ba178b8cf172..981dcb321f9e 100644
--- a/Microsoft/lvbs.config
+++ b/Microsoft/lvbs.config
@@ -6,3 +6,4 @@ CONFIG_DYNAMIC_DEBUG_CORE=n
 CONFIG_HEKI=y
 CONFIG_HYPERV=y
 CONFIG_HYPERV_VSM=y
+CONFIG_MODULE_SIG=y
-- 
2.43.0

